{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper. Score a crisscross pattern into each cut side of the eggplants, then sprinkle with salt and set aside for 30 minutes. Rinse salt from eggplants, dry well with a paper towel and place onto baking tray.","Preheat oven to 180°C.","Place harissa, garlic, turmeric, oregano, vinegar and 40 g of the oil into mixing bowl and blend <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Brush paste over eggplant flesh, ensuring paste gets into cuts. Bake for 50 minutes (180°C). Meanwhile, proceed with recipe. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place pistachios, bread and sumac into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add remaining 25 g oil and cook <b>3 min\/120°C\/speed 2<b>.","Remove eggplant from oven and sprinkle 2 tablespoons of the pistachio crumb over each eggplant. Bake for 10 minutes (180°C), until tender. Carefully transfer onto a serving platter, garnish with pomegranate arils just before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 eggplants, cut into halves lengthways","salt, for sprinkling","70 g harissa paste (see Tips)","2 garlic cloves","1 tsp ground turmeric","1 tsp dried oregano","2 tbsp apple cider vinegar","65 g extra virgin olive oil","70 g pistachio nuts","2 slices bread (approx. 70 g), torn into pieces","1 ½ tsp sumac","pomegranate arils, for garnishing (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r341781","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-6T8qXavG29M\/XZQu_xWtBUI\/AAAAAAAAcZg\/54cxvvk91yYCwl9--z91Gk8z0ClFPLr9QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_AeeBWU83h7CyvuZC.png","title":"Roasted eggplant","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.4 g","fat":"30 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"2.7 g","calories":"1744.6 kJ \/ 415.4 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, pastry brush, serving platter, paper towel, oven","hintsAndTricks":["You can find harissa in the international aisle of most major supermarkets. To make your own harissa, refer to the recipe on Cookidoo® (www.cookidoo.com.au).","For a milder version, replace the harissa with tomato paste.","Did you know you can use your Thermomix® to easily remove pomegranate arils? Go to the Thermomix in Australia YouTube channel to watch the video."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 35m","4 portions"]}